codex
Implemented [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](C:/Users/ColsonR/grid-bot-v2/.github/workflows/ci.yml#L1). It now runs on `push` and `pull_request` for `main` and `master`, sets up Python 3.12 with pip caching, installs `requirements.txt` plus `pytest`/`pytest-cov`, runs the full discovered pytest suite with a 60% coverage gate, generates `htmlcov`, and uploads that coverage report as an artifact.

I used plain pytest discovery instead of hard-coded file paths because this repo’s suite is split between root-level `test_*.py` files and `tests/test_*.py`; the sketched root paths for `test_state_machine.py` and `test_slot_engine.py` would not match this checkout. YAML validation passes locally with `python -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/workflows/ci.yml')); print('yaml-ok')"`. I could not run a local pytest collection here because `pytest` is not installed in this sandbox (`python -m pytest` fails with `No module named pytest`).
